🧠 Topic: Memory Hierarchy & Cache Memory

1️⃣ Concept Teaching (Strict, Clear, GATE-Oriented)
🔹 Memory Hierarchy

Memory in a computer is organized in levels based on:

👉 Speed
👉 Cost
👉 Size

🔹 Levels of Memory

From fastest to slowest:

1️⃣ Registers
2️⃣ Cache Memory
3️⃣ Main Memory (RAM)
4️⃣ Secondary Memory (HDD/SSD)

🔹 Key Idea

👉 Faster memory = smaller & expensive
👉 Slower memory = larger & cheaper

🔹 Locality of Reference (VERY IMPORTANT)

Programs tend to access:

1️⃣ Temporal Locality
Recently used data accessed again
2️⃣ Spatial Locality
Nearby memory locations accessed

📌 This is why cache works.

🔹 Cache Memory

A small, fast memory between CPU and main memory.

👉 Stores frequently used data
👉 Reduces access time

🔹 Cache Performance
🔹 Hit

Data found in cache

🔹 Miss

Data not found → fetched from main memory

