🔹 Types of Cache Mapping
1️⃣ Direct Mapping
Each block maps to exactly one cache line

📌 Simple but more collisions

2️⃣ Fully Associative Mapping
Block can go anywhere

📌 Flexible but costly

3️⃣ Set Associative Mapping
Combination of both

📌 Most practical system

🔹 Replacement Policies

When cache is full:

LRU (Least Recently Used)
FIFO (First In First Out)
Random

📌 LRU most common in GATE.

🔹 Write Policies
1️⃣ Write Through
Update cache + memory
2️⃣ Write Back
Update cache only (memory later)

📌 Write-back is faster.

🔹 Common GATE Traps
Confusing mapping techniques
Wrong AMAT formula
Mixing hit & miss ratio
